thames
------------------------------------------
thames is an ISIS-II emulator, allowing the tools used to build CP/M 3 to be
run under Unix.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.seasip.info/Unix/Thames/

Canonical download:
  https://www.seasip.info/Unix/Thames/thames-0.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack thames-0.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./thames-0.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/thames-0.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/thames-0.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(thames)
  /usr/bin/thames.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/thames.README
  /usr/share/doc/thames/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/thames/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/thames/thames.txt

